%N A394663 Decimal expansion of the constant characterizing the complexity of the general number field sieve (GNFS) factoring algorithm.
%C A394663 The GNFS algorithm has complexity O(exp(c*(log(n))^(1/3)*(log(log(n))^(2/3)))), where c is the present constant.
%H A394663 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A394663/b394663.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A394663 Carl Pomerance, <a href="https://www.ams.org/notices/199612/pomerance.pdf">A Tale of Two Sieves</a>, Notices of the American Mathematical Society, Volume 43, Number 12, December 1996, pp. 1473-1485 (see p. 1482).
%H A394663 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/NumberFieldSieve.html">Number Field Sieve</a>.
%H A394663 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_number_field_sieve">General number field sieve</a>.
%F A394663 Equals (64/9)^(1/3).
